                            <h5>A morning at the Monastery</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row">
                            <blockquote class="blockquote mb-0">
                                <p>
                                    The Batalha Monastery, a marvel of Gothic architecture, is a symbol of Portugal's independence, forged during the crucial Battle of Aljubarrota in 1385. Led by D. João I and General Nuno Álvares Pereira, the Portuguese triumphed against the larger forces number of D. João I of Castile, guaranteeing its independence. Construction of the Monastery began in 1388 and lasted 185 years, a testament to Portuguese devotion and architectural grandeur.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Accompanied by Mr. Portas, an 85-year-old gentleman, originally from Portugal but now residing in Brazil, and a dear friend of my husband Victor, we embarked on an exploration of the Monastery. Guided by experts, we were taken on a fascinating journey through the history of the Battle and the creation of the Monastery.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    The intricate details, sculptures, and stained glass of this monument left us in awe, evoking centuries of devotion and artistry. The stories shared by Mr. Portas, who displayed an enduring passion and extensive knowledge of the Monastery, enriched our experience.
                                </p>
                            </blockquote>
